[IOTDB-4796] Remove LoadStatistics consensus feature
body:
The LoadStatistics should not be consensus among the ConfigNode-Group for the following reasons:

1. They are easy to recompute within a short time.
2. The updation of LoadStatistics in the future might cause compatibility problems in the future.

Therefore, the LoadStatistics consensus feature will be abolished.

Changes in this PR:

1. The LoadStatistics consensus feature is abolished.
2. Adapt LoadStatistics check in new framework i.e. cache previousStatistics and calculate currentStatistics at the same time, thus the LoadManager can detect whether some LoadStatistics is changed.
3. Add formatted info level log in LoadManager when some LoadStatistics is changed. It's valuable to record the cluster load information and this process doesn't trigger frequently.

title: [IOTDB-4768] Balancing cluster RegionGroup leader distribution by MinimumCostFlow algorithm
body:
Balancing the cluster Region-leader distributiong by MinimumCostFlow algorithm.

The `RouteBalancer` starts a `Cluster-LeaderBalancing-Service`, and which will balance the leader distribution in every 5 loops of heartbeat service(5s per loop in default configuration). The leader distribution of SchemaRegion and DataRegion are calculated separately.

I've proved the optimality of MinimumCostFlow algorithm and the deficiency of greedy algorithm for the leader distribution problem at the [RegionGroup-leader balancing algorithm doc](https://apache-iotdb.feishu.cn/docx/doxcn6xa2p3bvqyF0cwBcit5fkh).

title: [IOTDB-4783] Optimize memory usage for LastFlushTimeManager

In fact, we can get latest time for each device from the working memtable to update the latestFlushTimeMap, so we can optimize memory usage of flushTimeManager by reducing the lastTimeMap.

title: [IOTDB-4341] Refactor LoadBalancing framework and maintain RegionRouteMap in RouteBalancer
body:
The LoadBalancing framework is now the same as the [Load balance framework](https://apache-iotdb.feishu.cn/docx/doxcnZ2tquzJKINQWi9nnYECPCb) doc.

I also fix ClusterIT bugs alone the way.

Mainly changes for LoadBalancing framework:

1. Move `versionTimestamp` and `isLeader` from RegionStatistics to RouteCache in RouteBalancer for  better structure decoupling.
2. Add `RegionRouteMap`, which consists from RegionLeaderMap and RegionPriorityMap, for future improvement.
3. Add `forceUpdate` interface both in NodeCache and RegionGroupCache and optimize the compute logic of UpdateLoadStatistics. Therefore, we can activate a newborn RegionGroup and mark a DataNode to be removed more easily and thread-safely.
4. Complement the `LoadBalancing framework`.

Update for ClusterIT:

1. Split `IoTDBConfigNodeIT` into `IoTDBClusterNodeIT`(with 2C2D environment) and IoTDBClusterAuthroizeIT(with 1C0D environment) to reduce test pressure.
5. Use 2C2D environment instead of 3C3D in `IoTDBConfigNodeSnapshotIT` to reduce test pressure.
6. Use 1C0D environment instead of 3C3D in `IoTDBStorageGroupIT` to to reduce test pressure.
7. Use MultiLeader consensus protocol in `IoTDBConfigNodeSwitchLeaderIT` to to reduce test pressure. (Since the Ratis protocol has the possibility to change leader during test).
8. Add `IoTDBClusterRegionLeaderBalancingIT`

title: [To rel/0.13] [IOTDB-4767] Support fetching all connection info in Session & SessionPool
body:
In this pr, I add a new interface to support fetching information of all the connections.
Each connection info will be like
```
struct TSConnectionInfo {
  1: required string userName
  2: required i64 logInTime
  3: required string connectionId // ip:port for thrift-based service and clientId for mqtt-based service
  4: required TSConnectionType type
}
```
If type is `THRIFT_BASED`, connectionId will be like `ip:port` style, and if type is `MQTT_BASED`, connectionId will just be `clientId` for MQTTClient.

## Description

### Content1 ...
Delete remote snapshot after region migration
### test
Test plan:
1. Enable the cluster 1C3D and two replicas
2. kiil drops the process where DataNode2 resides
3. Run the show regions command to view the replication information
4. Use the remove_node.sh script to remove DataNode2
5. Check whether snapshots are generated for the snapshot directories in DataNode1 and DataNode3
6. Wait for a period of time, and check whether the temporary file that completes the replica migration is deleted in DataNode1 and DataNode3. Run the show regions command to check whether the replica migration is correct
7. Connect to the datanode where the migrated replica resides to query data and verify that data is normal

title: [IOTDB-4736] Refactor process of show & drop functions
[IOTDB-2884]Redo Log for SchemaFile
body:
## Description
After https://github.com/apache/iotdb/pull/4732 merged, nodes of mtree could be swapped to disk when necessary in a format named SchemaFile which are organized as hierarchical B+Trees as [#5976](https://github.com/apache/iotdb/pull/5976) described. Since initiation of mtree still needs to scan all entries of mlog and apply it with corresponding actions, it may not be acceptable with massive mtree nodes. To enable the initiation from SchemaFile, there is an expected mechanism to keep SchemaFile integrity while flushing to disk, e.g., a redo log like module. And this pull request has provided such mechanism.

As the logging procedure may decay the performance, this pr also makes the segment size design more reasonable to be fit in one segmented page, and estimation of segment size more efficient if a bunch nodes are to be flushed as appended children. Last but not least, fixed size of SchemaFileLog (which acts like a redo log) is bound to around 256 MB(default) by restricting recorded pages, which is configurable in `iotdb-datanode.properties` identified as `schema_file_log_size`. Related formula is provided as well.

As long as this feature may be released and updated further, a version flag is added to the header of schema file.

title: [IOTDB-4681] speed up mpp load
body:
problem:
load is slower than write in 3C3D env, should be faster in theory.

solution:
- [x] only read TsFile once(speed up 60.86%)
In the origin implement, parse TsFile into many chunks, and when dispatching chunk, it will read from disk again. In new implement, it will only read TsFile once, when there is too many chunks in memory, it will dispatch chunks immediately.
- [x] only read CompressionType and TSEncoding while auto create schema in AnalyzeVisitor (optimize 8.09%)
Deserialize ChunkHeader cost too much time when auto create schema while only want the CompressionType and TSEncoding of a timeseries in parsing TsFile, but deserialize the measurement Id of this chunk is wasted. A new method is developed to only  
 read CompressionType nad TSEncoding of a timeseries.
- [x]  reduce the information of ChunkData to spend less time on serialize (optimize 6.90%)
There is some information can be analyzed from chunkHeader.
- [x] create a new method to generate TsFileResource faster (optimize 5.65%)
Origin TsFileResource generating method is using TimeseriesMetadata, and this is too slow for update time index of TsFileResource.
- [x] remove parse path in TsFileIOWriter.endFile()(optimize 49.06%)
see pr #7826

title: Rerun a new query execution thread while previous one is interrupted
body:
I found a strange thing in a timeout CI logs that there are no `Query-Worker-Thread-i` threads in thread dump file.
After digging into related codes, I found that if the `Query-Worker-Thread-i` is interrupted by others, it will exit quitely and will not print any logs. Then I refer to related codes in `Trino` and find that `Trino` will submit another execution thread in such case, so I did so in this pr.

title: [IOTDB-4741] [To rel/0.13] deprecate sessionId in all rpc requests
body:
Letting client claim its sessionId is not a good practice.

Using and manage a ClientSession to describe each connection on the server side is more safe.

Besides, Current timeout connection can not be closed by the server side, which may lead resource leakage if clients forget to close their connections. Therefore, we can close the socket connection to notify Thrift close the session.
